          longDescription: `SES defines three capability profiles. AI Base: SEND + WRITE + ATOMIC (no tag, no READ) for compute-bound collectives. AI Full: +TAGGED_SEND + READ + DEFERRABLE + RENDEZVOUS for richer buffering patterns. HPC (full superset): +wildcard tag matching for MPI compatibility. Request opcodes split into core semantics (send, write, read, atomic, rendezvous, collective) with profiles controlling availability. Header optimization: 44B standard carries full state (opcode, R_KEY, remote VA, JobID, match info); HPC-only 20B optimized omits match/message-ID/header-data for single-packet ops, saving 54% wire overhead. Response opcodes (RC_OK, RC_NO_MATCH, RC_BAD_MKEY, etc.) encode completion status + error class.`,
