              id: 'ordering-modes',
              label: 'Delivery Modes',
              short: 'PDM',
              description: 'Four PDS delivery modes: RUD/ROD/RUDI/UUD — Table 3-5 defines which profiles must support which modes.',
              longDescription: `Four delivery modes trade reliability + ordering vs throughput. RUD (all profiles): reliable but unordered; receiver reassembles OOO; sender sprays EV per-packet for load balance. ROD (AI Full/HPC): reliable + ordered; EV fixed at QP setup; serializes packets for strict ordering—lower throughput but TCP-like semantics. RUDI (HPC only): at-least-once delivery; NACK-only (no ACK); zero target state overhead; requires idempotent operations (barrier-based pipelines). UUD (all profiles): unreliable datagram fire-and-forget; used for telemetry. Single PDC binds to one mode + one traffic class (no mode mixing per PDC).`,
