              short: 'PCM',
              description: 'Vendor or operator-defined congestion logic executed in NIC control pipeline for workload-specific tuning beyond fixed NSCC/RCCC behavior.',
              longDescription: `PCM extends congestion control from fixed-function logic to policy-programmable execution while preserving wire compatibility. Operators can deploy custom objective functions (tail-latency minimization, fairness weighting by job class, burst damping for MoE traffic) using bounded update rules that map telemetry inputs to CWND/credit/path-weight outputs. Safety guards enforce finite update intervals, bounded gain, and rollback-on-instability so custom programs cannot destabilize the fabric. This enables cluster-specific optimization without changing UET packet formats or application APIs.`,
