          longDescription: `TSS in §3.7 is the transport security plane for confidentiality, integrity, anti-replay, and domain isolation. Security policy is endpoint-authoritative: transit network elements are untrusted and cannot be treated as cryptographic or correctness roots. Data-path rule is verify-before-use, with authenticated decryption on receive and explicit anti-replay sequence policy. Key management in §3.7.3-§3.7.5 uses SA lifecycle controls so long-lived high-rate sessions can rotate keys without pausing transport.`,
