              longDescription: `Encryption is endpoint-to-endpoint and runs inline in NIC pipeline, not as a software sidecar. Packet protection follows AEAD construction: ciphertext and authentication tag are generated in one operation and verified before payload enters transport semantics. Nonce uniqueness per (SA, direction) is mandatory; practical implementations use monotonic packet sequence/counter domains with rollover-triggered rekey before nonce exhaustion. Associated Data (AAD) binds routing/transport headers that remain in cleartext, so on-path header tampering still fails authentication. SA lifecycle is explicit: create, active, overlap-rekey, retire. Rekey policy is typically dual-threshold (time + packet-count) to cap exposure windows in long-running high-throughput jobs while avoiding transport stalls.`,
