      longDescription: `UET Link Layer adds three extensions to standard 802.3. (1) LLR: frame-sequence numbers in preamble; LLR_ACK frees replay buffer at transmitter; LLR_NACK triggers immediate retransmit; timeout guard ensures forward progress — lossless link delivery without PFC pause propagation. (2) CBFC: per-VC credit-based flow control; up to 32 VCs per port; sender uses credit for scheduling/adaptive routing; cyclic counter resilience to credit-message loss. (3) RS(544,514) FEC: mandatory for all link types; corrects up to 15-symbol errors per codeword; UCR/MTBPE statistics enable predictive monitoring.`,
